external_knowledge:
- Lighthouses metaphorically represent the surveys still active and guiding (lighthouse guiding ships) the annual health checks;
- Captains metaphorically represent the contact persons responsible for the surveys;
- Different regions refer to the geographic areas where the surveys are conducted;
- Charts follow the health indicators indicating the type of data being collected;
- The direction of the winds represents the indicator type, which in this case is 'Percent';
- Depth of the waters being charted metaphorically refers to the value of the measurements taken.

sql:
SELECT AVG(
    (CAST(SUBSTR(age_group, 1, INSTR(age_group, '-') - 1) AS REAL) + 
     CAST(SUBSTR(age_group, INSTR(age_group, '-') + 1) AS REAL)) / 2
) AS average_age_group
FROM survey_data;

SELECT DISTINCT indicator_name 
FROM indicators 
WHERE category = 'Lifestyle';
